All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Activity
Abstract super class of Course and Event that holds the common instance fields between the two title, meeting days, start time, and end time.
Conflict
Conflict interface that is used to handle scheduling conflicts between activities in WolfScheduler.
ConflictException
ConflictException is a checked exception that is thrown by Conflict interface if a conflict is present between Activities.
Course
Course object class that contains the name, title, section, credit hours, instructor's id meeting days, start time, and end time as private fields with their getters and setters.
CourseCatalog
This class is responsible for maintaining a catalog of courses.
CourseCatalogPanel
Creates a user interface for working with the CourseCatalog.
CourseNameValidator
Ensures that a course name is valid
CourseNameValidatorFSM
Finite State Machine for checking whether a Course's Name is valid.
CourseRecordIO
Writes into a file the Course records and reads Course records from files.
InvalidTransitionException
Class to handle invalid transitions in the finite state machine
PackSchedulerGUI
Main GUI for the PackScheduler project.
RegistrationManager
Class for handling Registration information.
Student
A class for creating Student objects, which hold information about the student
StudentDirectory
Maintains a directory of all students enrolled at NC State.
StudentDirectoryPanel
Creates a user interface for working with the StudentDirectory.
StudentRecordIO
A class for creating StudentRecordIO objects, which keep track of students.
User
Class for creating Users who operate pack scheduler
